band.summary: Todd Rundgren is an American musician, singer, songwriter, and record producer known for his diverse musical styles, sophisticated and often unconventional music, and early adoption of computer technologies. He began his career in the 1960s with the psychedelic band Nazz before pursuing a successful solo career. Rundgren is recognized as a pioneer in electronic music, progressive rock, and music videos.

event_name: Evann McIntosh @ Soho Restaurant & Music Club

band.summary: Evann McIntosh is an artist who blends dark alt-pop with R&B, incorporating elements of hip-hop, jazz, and funk. Their music explores themes of growth, gender identity, sexuality, and self-expression, characterized by insightful and unpredictable lyrics, as well as adventurous production. McIntosh's work is often described as intimate and a poignant portrait of modern adolescence. Their EP 'MOJO' gained significant traction, partly due to the viral TikTok success of the single "What Dreams Are Made Of."

San Lyon is a Los Angeles-based Swing Jazz Quartet that performs a blend of early 20th-century Parisian Gypsy Jazz and American Jazz standards, as well as original vintage-inspired songs. The band has been playing together since 2019 and has recorded several albums. The current members include Paige Herschell on vocals, kazoo, and melodica; Jenna Colombet on vocals, violin, and standup bass; Katie Cavera on vocals, standup bass, banjo, and guitar; and Dani Vargas on guitar, bass, and vocals.

Jenna Colombet is a Franco-American violinist, singer, bassist, and composer known for her versatile performances that blend swing jazz, folk, and classical music. She is a founding member and violinist of San Lyon, a swing jazz quartet based in Los Angeles, and has also played bass in the rock band Thou Shall Doubt. Colombet is also a composer, having written music for the musical tale "Vasilisa."

event_name: John Splithoff @ Soho Restaurant & Music Club

band.summary: John Splithoff is an American singer-songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, and music producer from Chicago, now based in Los Angeles. His music blends pop, neo-soul, and indie pop, characterized by soulful vocals, memorable melodies, and energetic rhythms. He released his debut album 'All In' in 2021 and his second album 'Far From Here' in March 2025. Splithoff has collaborated with various artists and achieved success with singles like 'Sing to You', which reached the Billboard Top 10.

They are known for their soulful vocal harmonies and energetic live performances, often incorporating improvisation and audience interaction.

They have released singles and EPs, and are known for their intense live performances.

event_name: Katie Kadan @ Clark Center For the Performing Arts

band.summary: Katie Kadan is a Chicago-born singer known for her powerful, soulful voice that blends gospel, blues, and soul with a modern twist. She gained national recognition on Season 17 of The Voice, where she became a finalist, impressing judges with her vocal range and emotional delivery. Kadan's music is characterized by heartfelt lyrics and a commanding stage presence.

Jakobs Castle, the project of Jakob Nowell (son of Sublime's Bradley Nowell), blends various genres including ska-punk, alternative rock, electropop, and power pop. His music is described as a modern interpretation of punk, incorporating elements of reggae and pop, inspired by both California's musical history and contemporary internet underground culture. The project aims to create cutting-edge music that is also palatable and infiltrates different scenes.

Alfred Robles is a Filipino-American stand-up comedian known for his relatable and observational humor often drawing from his experiences as a child of immigrants and his upbringing in Southern California. He has been featured on various comedy specials and television shows, and tours extensively.

Nekromantix is a Danish psychobilly band formed in Copenhagen in 1989 by Kim Nekroman. Their music often features horror and monster themes, and their distinctive image includes Nekroman's signature coffin-shaped bass. The band gained international recognition after signing with Hellcat Records in the early 2000s and has released several albums exploring their unique blend of punk, rockabilly, and horror.

Hot 45 is an R&B band based in San Luis Obispo, California, known for their dance grooves and love songs. The band was formed by singer-songwriter Reese Galido and features musicians from the Central Coast.

event_name: DJ Blu @ Oxnard Copper Blues Rock Pub & Kitchen

band.summary: DJ Blu is an American DJ and producer known for their versatile style, blending commercial dance, Top 40, and hip-hop. Hailing from the Memphis, TN area, DJ Blu has been spinning since the age of 11 and founded Blu Light Ent. in 1999. They have performed extensively across the southeastern United States and have had residencies on Rebel Radio. DJ Blu's music is often described as experimental and raw bass-influenced, incorporating elements of trap, hip hop, and dubstep.

David Franz is a California-based musician, producer, educator, and entrepreneur known for his work across various genres, including R&B, rock, hip-hop, blues, folk, world, and electronic music. He founded the record label Underground Sun, which aims to support emerging artists with a foundation in soul music. Franz also co-founded Underground Sol, dedicated to electronic music. His music often explores themes of personal transformation, connection, and seeking meaning.

band.summary: Fan Halen is recognized as the world's number one Van Halen tribute band, known for their authentic replication of Van Halen's look, sound, and energetic performances. They have performed internationally and opened for numerous established rock bands, and have been featured on AXS-TV's "The World's Greatest Tribute Bands."

event_name: Black Star @ The Majestic Ventura Theater

band.summary: Black Star is an American hip-hop duo formed in 1996, composed of rappers Yasiin Bey (formerly Mos Def) and Talib Kweli. They emerged from the underground hip-hop scene of the late 1990s, associated with Rawkus Records. Their critically acclaimed debut album, "Mos Def & Talib Kweli Are Black Star," was released in 1998, known for its conscious lyrics and alternative hip-hop sound. They have since released a second album, "No Fear of Time," in 2022.

Brian Swartz is a versatile and accomplished trumpeter, composer, arranger, and vocalist with a career spanning diverse musical landscapes including jazz, pop, and film scores. He has collaborated with numerous acclaimed artists and appeared on multiple Grammy-winning and nominated recordings. Swartz has released five jazz albums as a leader and is known for his original compositions and arrangements of jazz standards.

Matte Blvck is a San Diego-based electronic music trio formed in March 2020. They are known for blending brooding beats with an industrial edge, exploring genres such as breakbeats, industrial, darkwave, and cinematic dark pop. Their music is characterized by pulsing synths, mechanical percussion, and shadowy vocals, creating soundscapes that are both physical and introspective, existing between the club and the confessional. They have released two albums, 'I'm Waving, Not Drowning' (2020) and 'Vows' (2024), and have collaborated with artists like Clan of Xymox and Aaron Short. Their live performances are known for merging analogue and digital energy with striking visuals.

Mari Nobre is a versatile Jazz and Latin pop singer originally from Italy, who is also a Billboard-charted artist and has received a Latin Grammy certificate. She is known for her multilingual performances in English, Spanish, Portuguese, Italian, and French. Nobre is also the official singer for "Joyas Prestadas," the original band of Jenni Rivera. Her music blends Latin rhythms with pop and jazz influences, often featuring heartfelt lyrics and captivating beats. She has released albums such as "Sobran las Palabras" and "La Madrina."

band.summary: Jimmy Failla is an American stand-up comedian, television personality, and radio host. He is known for his work on "Fox & Friends" and his "Fox Across America" radio show.

Jane Monheit (born November 3, 1977) is an American jazz and traditional pop singer. She began her professional career at age 22 with her debut album "Never Never Land" in 2000, which became an instant success and established her as a prominent figure in jazz. Her singing has often been compared to Ella Fitzgerald, whom she cites as an influence. Monheit's repertoire includes jazz standards, classic pop songs, and Brazilian rhythms.
